title: Jaimason C. Trenholm
text:
Email: Jaimason.Trenholm@gmail.com
LinkedIn: Jaimason Trenholm
Phone: (737) 275-1732



Bachelor of Science in Business Management
Brigham Young University-Idaho, Rexburg, ID
- Culinary Arts - Data Science and Analytics - Business Finance - Minor in Small Business Operations





Aug. 2022 – Sep 2023
Life Care Services LLC, Georgetown, TX
- Prepared food items consistently and in compliance with recipes, portioning, cooking, and waste control guidelines. - Operated various kitchen appliances such as a blender, oven, grill, or stand mixer. - Ensured freshness of food and ingredients by checking for quality, keeping track of old and new items, and rotating stock. - Assisted in prep work, such as washing vegetables or butchering meat when needed. - Adhered to sanitation policies at all times when handling food products.



Aug. 2022 – Jun 2023
Georgetown ISD, Georgetown, TX
- Facilitated small group instruction and activities for students of varying abilities. - Supported teachers by preparing materials, setting up equipment, and organizing supplies. - Helped teacher plan lessons utilizing various teaching strategies including hands-on activities and technology integration.



May 2020 – Aug. 2022
Whataburger, Georgetown, TX
- Ensured cash values were consistent with sales and no money was lost. - Managed team on the floor, ensuring efficiency and timeliness. - Used customer service skills to provide customers with the best experience possible.





Competed in the state of Texas winning 1st place in the culinary division.
Helped rewrite the handbook for the Delaney, resulting in better training for new employees.
4 years of knife skills experience.
Helped manage funds and make food orders at the Delaney.
